Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.58,0:00:27.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Alright, we're ready.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.58,0:00:29.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We'll have Hattori sit there.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.94,0:00:32.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm kind of nervous.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.04,0:00:36.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He said he had some things to talk about, like the contract and the assistants.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.59,0:00:38.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's here!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.98,0:00:42.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Congrats on the serialization!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.26,0:00:44.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.93,0:00:46.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why is someone else here?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.85,0:00:48.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Does it have something to do with the contract?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.21,0:00:51.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm Miura. I've been with Jack since last year.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.67,0:00:52.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nice to meet you!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.47,0:00:54.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Y-Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.02,0:00:54.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Same here.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.95,0:00:57.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Miura will be supervising you two from now on.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.50,0:02:32.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.42,0:02:33.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You already have a place to work?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.91,0:02:35.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's great!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.34,0:02:38.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We got it from a relative who's a manga artist.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.60,0:02:41.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Really? How's the rent?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.78,0:02:41.97,Overlap,,0000,0000,0000,,Kawaguchi Tarou's workplace, huh.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.32,0:02:44.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's really cheap; about as much as the utility bills.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.93,0:02:45.51,Overlap,,0000,0000,0000,,That's great!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.51,0:02:48.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You could have rented a room with your signing bonus, but you've saved yourselves the trouble.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.85,0:02:50.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Great, great!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.39,0:02:50.99,Overlap,,0000,0000,0000,,Miura!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.31,0:02:52.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't be in such a rush.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.45,0:02:54.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,First, we have to discuss the transfer.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.11,0:02:55.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.92,0:02:59.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As I mentioned earlier,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.56,0:03:03.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Detective TRAP{\i0} will be supervised by Miura, not me.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.64,0:03:05.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.03,0:03:09.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm in charge of other serializations\N and also just took over One Piece.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.63,0:03:13.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It wouldn't be a good idea just to\N hand off these two to someone else.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.17,0:03:17.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's why he was assigned to this new project.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.44,0:03:20.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even though we've been in this together until now...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.36,0:03:25.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is there absolutely no way you can do it?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.70,0:03:26.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.81,0:03:29.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This isn't uncommon.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.89,0:03:34.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A little while ago, even a veteran author had their supervisor switched on them.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.08,0:03:38.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They protested to their editors, but were convinced eventually. {He?}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.41,0:03:40.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, I remember that.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.64,0:03:44.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They probably wouldn't even listen\N if new guys like you complained.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.14,0:03:47.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's alright! I'll do my best! Bring it on!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.97,0:03:51.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We'll be in your care.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.57,0:03:52.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please take care of us.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.50,0:03:53.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, leave it to me!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.43,0:03:55.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll get going, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.24,0:04:01.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's hard to keep a serialization going.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.15,0:04:03.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do your best, Ashirogi Muto!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.47,0:04:08.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Miura, I'll leave them to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.28,0:04:09.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.60,0:04:13.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hattori sure is cool.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.96,0:04:16.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It may not be unusual for this to happen, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.81,0:04:18.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You've got the wrong idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.40,0:04:25.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yesterday, he was begging so desperately to be allowed to work on Ashirogi Muto, they got angry with him.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.82,0:04:30.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hattori!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.19,0:04:38.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you for everything!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.40,0:04:39.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.31,0:04:46.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You'd better show me a good manga!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.32,0:04:48.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.28,0:04:52.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Bye.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.23,0:04:59.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My uncle said it too.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.68,0:05:06.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You can't do anything about an editor change, and getting used to one takes a while.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.66,0:05:10.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is the reality of being a professional.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.69,0:05:14.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Also, it bothers me that supervisors are like lottery tickets; you could end up with a winner or a loser.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.33,0:05:18.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hattori was definitely a winner.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.24,0:05:20.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey now, am I a loser?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.51,0:05:21.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, well..
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.44,0:05:23.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It'll be fine!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.35,0:05:24.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm still only 23!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.82,0:05:27.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's combine our youthful spirits and go for it!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.81,0:05:28.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.68,0:05:31.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That much?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.68,0:05:34.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Our contractual salary is that high?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.29,0:05:36.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's too much for you high schoolers.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.83,0:05:42.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you needed a place to work, we'd give you more money, but you guys already have one.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.38,0:05:43.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So you're not actually getting that amount.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.52,0:05:48.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well then, your script payment is ¥12,000 per page, with a 50% color page bonus.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.21,0:05:51.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? But I heard it was ¥9,000 for new authors.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.09,0:05:54.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's for non-serialized work. For serializations, it's ¥12,000.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.04,0:05:57.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Anyways, stop interrupting and listen. These are the arrangements.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.26,0:05:58.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.47,0:06:00.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The copyright belongs to Yueisha.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.85,0:06:03.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No other magazine may publish your work.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.80,0:06:04.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.91,0:06:07.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We don't have the leisure to draw for another magazine!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.42,0:06:11.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Quite the opposite - since our annual contract is with you, I want to make sure it runs continuously for the whole year.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.81,0:06:13.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's the spirit!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.33,0:06:16.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll bring a proper contract next time, so you can sign it then.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.42,0:06:17.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.72,0:06:20.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's also the problem of your assistants,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.22,0:06:24.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but I managed to get a pro named Ogawa. He's talented.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.77,0:06:28.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But I don't have many new people, so I've got no other talented people to give you.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.91,0:06:30.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you have anyone you know who could help you?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.91,0:06:32.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Someone who dabbles in manga or something.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.12,0:06:34.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Acquaintances?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.74,0:06:35.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ishizawa?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.72,0:06:37.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No way.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.91,0:06:41.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Having someone assist you with the\N inking and tone would help a lot.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.40,0:06:43.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe Miyoshi?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.45,0:06:44.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She's our last resort.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.15,0:06:47.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Alright, I'll handle it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.11,0:06:50.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll find two young people with serious personalities.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.85,0:06:51.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.61,0:06:54.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Um, how much does it cost for an assistant?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.85,0:06:56.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, that's important.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.59,0:06:58.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A young assistant costs ¥10,000 per day.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.78,0:07:01.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,About ¥160,000 per month working four days per week.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.96,0:07:04.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,At the most, Ogawa would cost you ¥380,000 per month.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.99,0:07:06.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,¥380,000?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.94,0:07:10.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,These days, you can only pull people in with that kind of salary, so it can't be helped.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.52,0:07:14.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It requires a high skill level, and he'll direct and supervise the other assistants for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.83,0:07:17.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Also, assistants have expenses like travel and food.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.31,0:07:18.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Until it's published, we're in the red!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.95,0:07:20.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If it gets canceled before then, we'll stay in the red!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.44,0:07:24.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please don't talk about being in debt when we've just been serialized.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.55,0:07:25.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh yeah, sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.36,0:07:29.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's see, is it alright if they stay over here?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.05,0:07:32.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's only enough space in the next room to nap.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.77,0:07:37.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My uncle did a gag manga, so the assistants just went home the next day.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.40,0:07:41.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Your uncle was successful enough\N for assistants? What's his name?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.10,0:07:42.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,His name's Kawaguchi Tarou...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.52,0:07:44.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.98,0:07:48.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The author of that {\i1}Super Hero Legend {\i0}?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.49,0:07:51.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.53,0:07:53.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's why that poster's here!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.53,0:07:54.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Awesome!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.78,0:07:56.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So that work was born here!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.90,0:07:59.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I really loved it when I read it in middle school!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.09,0:08:02.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm so impressed!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.24,0:08:05.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm expecting even more from you now that I know your uncle is Kawaguchi Tarou!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.03,0:08:07.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Next comes the schedule.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.92,0:08:10.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The deadline is two weeks before Jack goes on sale.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.80,0:08:14.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, two weeks before \Nthe Monday that the issue is released.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.86,0:08:19.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ideally, we want the finished \Nmanuscript by the Friday before that.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.57,0:08:22.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The final deadline for {\i1}TRAP{\i0}  is February 4th.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.12,0:08:25.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The first volume is 54 pages. The second is 27.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.36,0:08:28.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It really only has to be 25, but  you wanted a bit more?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.37,0:08:29.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, we'll take care of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.48,0:08:31.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'd like you to turn that in as soon as possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.88,0:08:34.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I want to wait for the survey results for Volume 4 onwards, so we won't get into those yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.07,0:08:37.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you fine with the assistants starting at the beginning of the year?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.87,0:08:39.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.14,0:08:43.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.96,0:08:43.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's going through this so fast. Is this guy a winner?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.62,0:08:45.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We can't have you lose to them!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.49,0:08:51.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Um... Hiramaru Kazuya of {\i1}Otters 11{\i0} is new, like us, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.80,0:08:53.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What kind of person is he?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.46,0:08:58.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I haven't met him yet, but according to the editorial department, he quit his job as a salary man to do manga.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.49,0:08:59.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Quitting an office job?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.56,0:09:03.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It seems that at the age of 26, he suddenly quit his job and started drawing manga.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.20,0:09:09.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Without having read much manga before then, his first work got honorable mention in a monthly contest.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.24,0:09:11.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A genius on another level like Niizuma.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.99,0:09:14.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Great things are expected from him more than anyone else.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.19,0:09:16.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,More than anyone else?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.12,0:09:17.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,More than Eiji?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.94,0:09:21.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, it's alright!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.02,0:09:23.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Otters{\i0} is like a gag manga,\N and it has a different writing style.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.67,0:09:27.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Besides, there's no use comparing\N different manga with each other!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.11,0:09:30.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All that matters is that yours is good.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.18,0:09:32.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.16,0:09:33.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I think so too!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.72,0:09:36.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We'll give it our all!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.77,0:09:39.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Alright! You guys are still young!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.09,0:09:40.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're gonna flare up and burn out!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.13,0:09:43.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Um, we don't want to burn out...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.04,0:09:46.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, that was a slip of the tongue. Don't worry about it!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.55,0:09:49.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is he a winner or loser?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.12,0:09:51.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He doesn't seem like a bad guy.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.18,0:09:52.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just one more thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.24,0:09:55.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,January 17th is the New Year's party.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.98,0:09:57.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,New Year's party?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.36,0:09:58.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are we invited too?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.61,0:10:01.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All serialized manga authors attend!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.25,0:10:06.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If authors don't attend without a good reason, the editors in charge of them won't have it easy!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.07,0:10:07.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,New Year's party...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.37,0:10:10.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm happy, but nervous!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.12,0:10:13.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's not a problem of being nervous!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.10,0:10:15.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, a car will be coming to pick you up.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.05,0:10:16.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A car?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.32,0:10:21.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A car's picking you up, huh? Serialized manga authors are pretty amazing.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.34,0:10:24.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Today's our meeting with the\N assistants. I'm kind of nervous.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.26,0:10:28.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shouldn't I come then?  I could do odd jobs.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.79,0:10:30.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You'd calm down if a girl was there!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.80,0:10:30.56,Overlap,,0000,0000,0000,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.50,0:10:33.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There will only be men working today; five of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.54,0:10:34.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is a man's workplace.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.16,0:10:36.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It'll be different from before.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.16,0:10:39.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Alright. I'll refrain.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.32,0:10:45.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is the chief assistant, Ogawa.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.66,0:10:47.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nice to meet you.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.19,0:10:48.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And this is Kato.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.83,0:10:50.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's an honor to meet you!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.83,0:10:52.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll be in your care.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.14,0:10:53.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Also...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.11,0:10:53.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Miura!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.99,0:10:56.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You didn't say anything about a girl coming!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.13,0:10:59.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kato only lives 3 train stops from\N here. She won't be staying the night.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.56,0:11:04.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And she has a year of experience as an\N assistant in both shoujo and shounen manga.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.11,0:11:06.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You won't find another person with that much experience!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.09,0:11:07.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.57,0:11:10.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You'll get distracted if there's a girl here?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.10,0:11:10.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Silly young man.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.82,0:11:12.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's not it! But my girlfriend...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.96,0:11:14.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.60,0:11:14.86,Overlap,,0000,0000,0000,,Should we get Miyoshi to do the inking?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.21,0:11:19.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And that's Takahama. He's 19.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.69,0:11:22.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Of the people under me, he's the best at drawing.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.92,0:11:25.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He avoided my gaze!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.83,0:11:29.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He works fast and has unlimited potential as an assistant.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.58,0:11:31.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Doesn't that mean he has no experience?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.58,0:11:33.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well then, Ogawa.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.11,0:11:33.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Alright.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.52,0:11:36.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We're short one desk.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.14,0:11:37.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And a tracer.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.97,0:11:40.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The copier is old, but it looks like it will be fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.83,0:11:43.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sensei, where is the computer and printer?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.34,0:11:44.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Computer?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.03,0:11:44.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We don't have one here.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.59,0:11:47.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There are quite a few reference books here,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.71,0:11:50.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but it's best for {\i1}Detective TRAP {\i0}'s\N backgrounds to be realistic.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.44,0:11:53.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'd like to take pictures of scenery with a digital camera, edit and trace them here.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.45,0:11:55.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Got it. I'll arrange it right away.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.12,0:11:55.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's okay, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.93,0:11:57.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, yes, please do.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.68,0:12:00.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, you already have a penned-in manuscript.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.04,0:12:04.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tako, Takahama.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.62,0:12:06.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Finish up one page each.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.92,0:12:11.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then, matching their art, draw other characters.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.18,0:12:12.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.74,0:12:17.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Awesome! So this is a pro assistant!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.58,0:12:18.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I know, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.88,0:12:19.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sensei.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.72,0:12:21.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you weak at drawing right-facing faces?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.53,0:12:23.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, I sketch them in reverse.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.97,0:12:24.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.92,0:12:30.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Regardless of that, look at the whole manuscript in reverse and check for deviances.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.02,0:12:33.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Though you're good at it, a little discrepancy stands out.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.88,0:12:35.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, that's enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.64,0:12:39.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll do most of the backgrounds and spread the work among the three of us.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.33,0:12:41.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And I'll leave the characters to Takahama.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.68,0:12:43.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Finishing will be done by the person with less work.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.72,0:12:47.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Miura, if the first volume is 54 pages, and the second is 27,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.49,0:12:49.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,we should turn this in soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.96,0:12:52.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's really great!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.32,0:12:54.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I have to work hard!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.81,0:12:56.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's our first serialization!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.07,0:13:06.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I borrowed my brother's suit...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.30,0:13:08.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is it really that strange?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.50,0:13:11.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You look like a salary man. I'm going in this.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.62,0:13:12.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you serious?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.56,0:13:14.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They said to come in everyday clothes.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.46,0:13:16.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You can't take that seriously.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.30,0:13:21.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't you think it's rude to greet the authors without wearing appropriate clothes?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.17,0:13:23.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Y-You think so?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.32,0:13:27.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is this the Ashirogi residence?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.22,0:13:28.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.91,0:13:33.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll be assisting you today. I'm Tanaka from Metropolitan Transportation.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.14,0:13:34.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.72,0:13:38.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's already been waiting for 15 minutes?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.02,0:13:39.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He said he got here early to avoid being late!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.70,0:13:41.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I feel bad for making him wait, so let's hurry up!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.11,0:13:41.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, wait up!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.65,0:13:45.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You are Ashirogi, correct?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.17,0:13:45.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please step inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.18,0:13:47.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,O-Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.26,0:13:51.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If we leave now, we'll get there 40 minutes early.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.60,0:13:54.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But I can arrange for us to arrive at a more suitable time.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.40,0:13:55.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What would you like?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.56,0:13:59.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,W-Well then, we would like to arrive 15 minutes early.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.77,0:14:01.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Understood.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.50,0:14:08.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Being driven around like this makes me feel extra nervous.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.68,0:14:10.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right, I need to practice.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.15,0:14:14.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Greetings. My name is Takagi of the pair of authors under the name Ashirogi Muto,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.64,0:14:20.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,creators of the manga Detective TRAP\N which will begin serialization in February.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.84,0:14:22.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's a pleasure to meet you.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.11,0:14:24.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't it kind of long?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.04,0:14:25.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.03,0:14:26.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can just finish with "I'm Mashiro".
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.88,0:14:28.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No fair!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.20,0:14:29.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You should talk too!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.65,0:14:31.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No way, it's not my thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.17,0:14:31.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why not?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.45,0:14:35.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We've arrived.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.25,0:14:42.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's with this gathering of suspicious black cars?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.30,0:14:43.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Scary!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.85,0:14:44.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Welcome.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.98,0:14:47.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you have any belongings, you\N may leave them in the cloak room.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.17,0:14:49.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please take this number card with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.99,0:14:51.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,O-Okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.40,0:14:52.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, you're here.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.45,0:14:54.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Miura, Hattori!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.51,0:14:58.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank goodness. I feel kind of out of place.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.01,0:14:59.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is some place!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.92,0:15:03.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If your serialization continues,\N you'll come here every year!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.08,0:15:04.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You get used to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.26,0:15:06.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Niizuma is already here.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.82,0:15:11.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shinohara! It's been a while!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.70,0:15:14.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, really out of place...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.04,0:15:15.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ashirogi!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.90,0:15:20.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Have a belated "Happy New Year!"
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.89,0:15:22.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Niizuma!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.16,0:15:23.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's in his usual sweats!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.40,0:15:25.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Minors mustn't drink.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.61,0:15:27.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's plenty of juice.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.37,0:15:29.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is also juice.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.01,0:15:29.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Japan!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.48,0:15:33.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.49,0:15:35.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Was there an editor who looked like that?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.37,0:15:38.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's my new friend, Hiramaru.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.54,0:15:39.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,New friend?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.41,0:15:42.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hiramaru?! That's him?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.95,0:15:42.18,Overlap,,0000,0000,0000,,You just randomly approached me.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.83,0:15:44.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's the genius who may even be better than Eiji!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.51,0:15:47.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nice to meet you! We're Ashirogi Muto!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.76,0:15:49.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nice to meet you!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.29,0:15:53.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you classmates of his? Is it alright to bring friends to the New Year's party?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.33,0:15:55.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Both of them are authors.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.66,0:15:57.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The artist and writer of Ashirogi Muto.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.68,0:15:59.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Two in one!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.07,0:16:01.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Really. There are a lot of young manga authors.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.98,0:16:04.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry about that, sensei.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.90,0:16:08.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,At any rate, I've come to a pretty strange place.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.90,0:16:10.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This place is great.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.52,0:16:12.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's a lot of delicious food.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.39,0:16:15.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's like I took a wrong turn. Not on the highway, but in life.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.93,0:16:19.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's no way I can be a manga author.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.74,0:16:22.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"No way"? Didn't you want\N to become a manga author?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.91,0:16:26.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Did I want to? For a moment I did think that.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.71,0:16:28.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I was briefly possessed by the idea, you might say.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.88,0:16:33.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,One day, when I was tired of going to work, I picked up an edition of Jack and thought I could do it, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.54,0:16:37.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Jeez, what the hell was I doing? I screwed up.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.90,0:16:40.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He thinks he screwed up even though he was serialized?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.19,0:16:42.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey you, bring me another!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.63,0:16:43.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.73,0:16:46.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then what did you want to do?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.24,0:16:48.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I just didn't want to work.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.36,0:16:52.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But now I've got a monthly\N serialization. That's impossible.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.75,0:16:55.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why do people have to work?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.65,0:16:57.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I just want to sleep and eat.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.70,0:17:00.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I should have been born as a panda in a zoo!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.22,0:17:03.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, is that why it's called {\i1}Otter 11{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.19,0:17:08.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see. Subconsciously, I think the otter in the aquarium is better off than a human.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.40,0:17:10.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hiramaru, there you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.91,0:17:12.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Damn, it's him.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.44,0:17:16.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's the one who flattered me by saying "You have talent" and "You're a genius!"
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.56,0:17:16.06,Overlap,,0000,0000,0000,,Before the party gets going,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.05,0:17:17.30,Overlap,,0000,0000,0000,,let's talk about the problem spots in the third volume...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.39,0:17:20.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yoshitashi! Do you think it's good to be alive?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.46,0:17:23.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Alright, lets go with that.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.15,0:17:24.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The catchphrase of your third volume...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.91,0:17:27.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hiramaru is kind of weird and interesting.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.88,0:17:29.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.73,0:17:31.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's about to start, so come up to the front...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.73,0:17:33.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? What's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.58,0:17:36.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Uh, we were just hit by Hiramaru's bad mood.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.80,0:17:37.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Bad mood?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.56,0:17:40.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Speaking of which, he did say serialization was impossible.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.12,0:17:45.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, there are certainly people who are\N uncertain when they get serialized so suddenly.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.00,0:17:47.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But once you start up, it'll all work out.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.30,0:17:49.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You two will be fine!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.76,0:17:50.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Probably.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.50,0:17:58.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Excuse me, everyone. Thank you all for taking time out of your busy schedules to come here.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.17,0:18:01.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you for allowing me to be your host for this New Year's party.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.70,0:18:06.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My name is Aida Soichi, and I work in Shounen Jack's editorial department.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.54,0:18:08.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Champagne for the toast?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.18,0:18:09.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you very much.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.00,0:18:12.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's pretend to drink it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.56,0:18:13.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nice attitude.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.78,0:18:15.52,Overlap,,0000,0000,0000,,First of all, let's have a few words from Mr. Torishima of the Board of Directors.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.18,0:18:21.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's who Arare-chan's Mashirito and S{\i1}uper Hero Legend{\i0}'s Torishiman are based on!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.62,0:18:24.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm Torishima.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.83,0:18:28.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Torishima was a model for chief\N editors while I was working there.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.80,0:18:33.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I was happy when he came up to me at the New Years party, asked "Who said you could put me in there?!", and strangled me.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.76,0:18:35.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You were happy?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.00,0:18:36.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We're good friends.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.85,0:18:39.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And now I'm at the same New Year's party.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.90,0:18:41.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you very much.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.92,0:18:43.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are we done already?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.15,0:18:45.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Another few words, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.46,0:18:46.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.56,0:18:49.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well then, continuing on,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.11,0:18:53.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'd like to ask Akimoto to lead the toast on behalf of all the authors.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.16,0:18:55.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Cheers!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.61,0:18:58.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm going to eat a lot.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.54,0:19:00.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Niizuma, you took too much-
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.16,0:19:02.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, there's delicious-looking stuff over there too!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.50,0:19:05.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you perhaps Ashirogi?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.77,0:19:06.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.97,0:19:10.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My name's Arai. My {\i1}Baked Cheese{\i0} manga is getting serialized the volume before yours.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.84,0:19:12.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nice to meet you. I'm Takagi.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.88,0:19:13.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm Mashiro.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.92,0:19:15.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Pleased to make your acquaintance.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.60,0:19:17.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You are high schoolers, I hear?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.18,0:19:17.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.91,0:19:19.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Its nice to be fresh-faced.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.76,0:19:22.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, I was just thinking of taking them around to meet everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.98,0:19:25.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see. It's tough for newcomers.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.46,0:19:26.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do your best.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.45,0:19:27.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.31,0:19:29.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oishi, can I talk to you for a minute?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.65,0:19:31.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, that's fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.06,0:19:32.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Manga should be interesting.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.61,0:19:36.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,61!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.06,0:19:37.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Number 61!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.45,0:19:38.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Does anyone have Bingo?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.84,0:19:39.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Bingo.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.86,0:19:40.19,Overlap,,0000,0000,0000,,It's number 61!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.19,0:19:40.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you serious?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.37,0:19:44.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Our first winner, Takagi. Which prize would you like?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.81,0:19:48.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Um... the TV.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.41,0:19:50.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The special prize right off the bat!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.94,0:19:54.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's perfect, since the TV in our workplace is still analog.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.13,0:19:58.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Being a manga author really is about\N hard work, self-confidence, and luck!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.17,0:20:00.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,More like hard work, conceit, and luck.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.53,0:20:02.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But maybe we've used up our luck with this.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.63,0:20:03.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't say things like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.79,0:20:05.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I hear you won't give the go ahead for an anime yet?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.85,0:20:10.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yuujirou said that an anime will catch up to the manga soon, so I shouldn't do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.04,0:20:11.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's unexpectedly cautious.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.65,0:20:13.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Niizuma, will you give me your autograph?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.59,0:20:15.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,One of my relatives is a fan.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.21,0:20:17.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sure. Who should I make it out to?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.90,0:20:18.22,Overlap,,0000,0000,0000,,Niizuma Eiji looks like he's having fun.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.22,0:20:19.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is he delaying an anime adaptation?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.11,0:20:22.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's already become a real, serious manga author.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.02,0:20:25.24,Overlap,,0000,0000,0000,,Niizuma! Talk to me more! Reassure me!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.13,0:20:25.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Can we be like that?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.24,0:20:26.32,Overlap,,0000,0000,0000,,Niizuma!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.59,0:20:30.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I want to be able to come here every year.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.95,0:20:33.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, we'll definitely come back.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.58,0:20:37.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,For that, you need to work hard on your serialization.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.76,0:20:38.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hattori!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.91,0:20:40.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well? Have you gotten a bit used to it?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.04,0:20:43.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, well, somehow.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.31,0:20:45.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The people here are really charismatic, and we got a bit overwhelmed.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.95,0:20:48.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is a great opportunity. Enjoy it.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.99,0:20:51.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you like, there's an after party, and an after-after party!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.66,0:20:53.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is the only one high schoolers should attend.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.04,0:20:55.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't give them undue temptations.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.62,0:20:56.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Editor-in-Chief!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.80,0:20:58.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, well, that was...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.00,0:21:00.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mashirito!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.54,0:21:03.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is Mashiro and Takagi. Their serialization begins this year.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.39,0:21:11.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kawaguchi Tarou.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.17,0:21:13.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What happened to him was a shame.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.25,0:21:17.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As someone who worked with him, I can only feel regret.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.14,0:21:22.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He was a man with guts. You could say that backfired on him.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.23,0:21:24.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.46,0:21:28.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm glad to have the opportunity to serialize people like you two.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.18,0:21:29.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do your best.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.94,0:21:30.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.01,0:21:36.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'd like to do the things my uncle couldn't do, and the things he left undone.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.99,0:21:38.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What he couldn't do?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.76,0:21:40.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What he left undone?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.61,0:21:43.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What he couldn't do was make a living off of manga alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.08,0:21:47.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What he left undone was getting first place in the survey!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.99,0:21:49.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How promising.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.70,0:21:52.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The best chance of getting first place in the survey is in the first year of serialization.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.60,0:21:58.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No. Popular manga authors want to get the top spot {\i1}and{\i0} have a long-running series.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.17,0:21:59.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No matter how long it takes.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.44,0:22:04.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The possibility isn't zero.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.63,0:22:08.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Rather than thinking that, you think the possibilities are infinite.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.65,0:22:14.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Instead of thinking "I'd like to make that a reality", you think "By my actions, I'll make it a reality".
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.47,0:22:16.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I heard that from some movie.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.31,0:22:17.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.86,0:22:19.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Though the party is in full swing,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.76,0:22:21.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's over.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.11,0:22:22.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Goodbye.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.76,0:22:22.83,Overlap,,0000,0000,0000,,unfortunately it's about time to wrap things up.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.00,0:22:23.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you very much!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.82,0:22:26.19,Overlap,,0000,0000,0000,,We reserved the hall for a short time...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:26.19,0:22:29.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:25.62,0:22:27.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Number one on the survey?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.54,0:22:29.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sending a text to Azuki...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:29.47,0:22:31.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So I don't forget the determination I had today!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:37.42,0:22:38.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mashiro...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.55,0:24:17.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Our serialization is about to start, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:17.19,0:24:18.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...our supervisor got changed, and then...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:18.81,0:24:19.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's something else?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:19.73,0:24:21.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Azuki, why did you send that text?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:21.80,0:24:23.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What text?!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:23.06,0:24:25.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Next time, "Anthologies and Photo Albums"
Dialogue: 0,0:24:25.07,0:24:27.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Which is more important, dreams or reality?
